<h2>12. 4-Week Documentation & Development Plan (Frontend & Documentation Focus)</h2>

<h3>Week 1: Frontend Analysis & Architecture</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Goal:</strong> Full understanding of the frontend codebase and architectural mapping.</li>
    <li><strong>Tasks:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Map out the complete frontend component hierarchy and routing structure.</li>
            <li>Audit <code>TanStack Query</code> implementation for state management efficiency.</li>
            <li>Document the "As-Is" frontend architecture.</li>
            <li>Identify reusable UI components and potential duplication in <code>shadcn/ui</code> usage.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<h3>Week 2: UI/UX & Quality Assurance</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Goal:</strong> Deep dive into User Interface consistency and validation logic.</li>
    <li><strong>Tasks:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Audit all forms for Zod validation coverage and error handling consistency.</li>
            <li>Verify responsive design behavior across mobile, tablet, and desktop breakpoints.</li>
            <li>Review <code>Tailwind CSS</code> usage for consistency (colors, spacing, typography).</li>
            <li>Cleanup hardcoded strings and move them to constants or configuration files.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<h3>Week 3: Frontend Performance & Optimization</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Goal:</strong> Optimizing client-side performance and user experience.</li>
    <li><strong>Tasks:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Implement code splitting and lazy loading for heavy routes (e.g., Partner/Admin Dashboards).</li>
            <li>Optimize image loading strategies (lazy loading, size attributes) via Cloudinary integration.</li>
            <li>Audit and optimize bundle size (remove unused dependencies).</li>
            <li>Enhance accessibility (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation) across the application.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<h3>Week 4: Finalization & Handover</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Goal:</strong> Polish, Documentation, and Release Preparation.</li>
    <li><strong>Tasks:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Finalize this technical documentation.</li>
            <li>Create visual data flow and component hierarchy diagrams.</li>
            <li>Prepare frontend deployment guide (Vercel configuration, environment variables).</li>
            <li>Conduct a final code review and formatting pass (Prettier/ESLint).</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

</body>
